   Hello,
	   I am interested in a software implementation of the RSA optimised
   to run on an 8-bit micro-processor with limited memory. 

   If anyone has pointers to papers, articles, commercial s/w etc. I would appreciate
   recieving some information. 

There was an article in Dr. Dobbs Journal, written by Burt Kaliski
(sorry if I mispelled that, Burt) of RSADSI, which is an optimised
modmult for 8-bit architecture.  It was printed last summer, and it
includes code (I think 8080 assembly, or somthing like that).

